<br>
There is nice, and there is silly. That was silly. That was the only &quot;good&quot; thing that happened to you and you GAVE it away. *sigh*. I would have appologized because the spawn did jump me and I would have had to defend yourself but I would not give up the loot. You did nothing wrong.<br>
<br>
Sol A is tough. I tried to solo it a bit last night with my Druid and had to zone a few times. Stuff at zone is blue at 24.<br>
<br>
My Rogue can solo there, but only carefully as Gobos by nature tend to be VERY aggro. Even at 44 stuff at zone swarms me. Best bet here, get camo'd go to barroom and get BEHIND the bar. Not even the 2 spawns facing you will aggro and the only spawn you need to directly deal with is what ever is behind the bar. <p><body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>

